The paper addresses the problem of adversarial examples in machine learning, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method uses the minimum description length (MDL) principle, which is a well-known principle in information theory and machine learning, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the method is for static malware detection, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and security and privacy (cs.SI) sub-categories.
